<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4928506>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 11–12. Metaphalangium spp., detail of the anterior prosoma and pedipalps. 11 Metaphalangium martensi sp. n. (holotype, SIZK K-3197, from Rovno amber, Klesov, Pugach quarry, Ukraine; late Eocene). Note the palpal patella with small and blunt medio-distal prominence (black arrow) with stout spine-like setae and mesial brush of stout spine-like setae on palpal tibia (white arrow), ventral view. 12 Comparative image of the extant species Metaphalangium cirtanum (C. L. Koch) (juvenile from Albania: Zvërnec), white arrows indicate palpal patella and tibia, mesially covered with stout spine-like setae, dorso-lateral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4928506/files/figure.png" .

